description: From Latin subsecutus, past participle of subsequi. See subsequent.

verbs.description: subsecute (third-person singular simple present subsecutes, present participle subsecuting, simple past and past participle subsecuted)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To follow closely, or so as to overtake; to pursue.
